WEBVTT

01:27.480 --> 01:30.907
<i>"We danced our youth
in a dreamed-of city</i>

01:32.610 --> 01:33.804
<i>Venice</i>

01:34.044 --> 01:36.444
<i>Paradise proud and pretty</i>

01:45.789 --> 01:48.986
<i>We lived for love and lust and beauty</i>

01:49.193 --> 01:51.559
<i>Pleasure then our only duty</i>

02:03.474 --> 02:06.102
<i>Floating then 'twixt heaven and earth</i>

02:06.310 --> 02:08.972
<i>And drunk on plenty's blessed mirth</i>

02:21.358 --> 02:23.918
<i>We thought ourselves eternal then</i>

02:24.161 --> 02:26.925
<i>Our glory sealed by God's own pen</i>

02:35.005 --> 02:37.769
<i>But paradise we found is always frail</i>

02:40.444 --> 02:43.345
<i>Against man's fear will always fail. "</i>

03:02.032 --> 03:03.761
Is anything wrong, Mama?

03:04.301 --> 03:05.700
Nothing at all.

03:23.854 --> 03:25.185
I feel faint.

03:25.556 --> 03:27.023
I feel faint.

03:29.660 --> 03:30.820
I feel faint.

03:36.734 --> 03:37.928
What are you doing?

03:38.168 --> 03:39.692
Come on, Beatrice.

03:41.905 --> 03:42.997
Quick!

03:47.878 --> 03:49.345
Slow down!

03:51.682 --> 03:52.706
Veronica!

04:12.636 --> 04:13.261
Look!

04:13.704 --> 04:14.762
Hello!

04:14.905 --> 04:15.929
Your brother!

04:16.173 --> 04:17.902
Hello, Venice!

04:18.275 --> 04:19.742
What if he sees us?

04:19.977 --> 04:22.172
He's looking at them, not us.

04:22.379 --> 04:24.643
Hello, Venice!

04:25.449 --> 04:26.973
Did you get my letters?

04:27.217 --> 04:30.186
No? I'm not talking to you anyway.
You broke my heart.

04:30.521 --> 04:31.783
Come on!

04:39.196 --> 04:40.527
Come on!

04:46.804 --> 04:48.294
All this for me?

04:53.377 --> 04:54.844
Oh Olivia

04:55.112 --> 04:56.238
Oh glorious maid

04:56.547 --> 04:57.809
Of virtue spare

04:58.015 --> 05:00.006
With bosoms like those who could care?

05:02.152 --> 05:03.278
My rod...

05:03.587 --> 05:05.555
...my lady, a hand.

05:08.392 --> 05:09.256
- Come.
- Hardly.

05:17.267 --> 05:19.792
It's Venus, come to bless the Venetians!

05:35.886 --> 05:37.148
You smell like a sewer.

05:37.354 --> 05:41.017
Thank you. That's a fine welcome,
little sister. Look at you.

05:41.258 --> 05:42.919
You might make a wife after all.

05:43.160 --> 05:44.491
- Did you see him?
- Who?

05:47.764 --> 05:48.924
Is he handsome?

05:52.202 --> 05:54.033
- He's powerful.
- He is.

06:02.846 --> 06:04.404
Welcome home, Marco.

06:13.724 --> 06:15.191
I think I've missed you.

06:15.659 --> 06:17.786
With all the court ladies to amuse you?

06:18.028 --> 06:21.259
Roman women, they can't hold a candle
to the Venetian.

06:21.965 --> 06:25.332
Nor can French, Florentine
nor any from Europe to the Levant.

06:25.802 --> 06:27.667
No doubt you've sampled them all.

06:27.871 --> 06:30.237
All but idle amusement
until you blossomed.

06:31.508 --> 06:33.976
What keeps a son
from greeting his own parents?

06:34.244 --> 06:36.041
Beauty, I think.

06:38.749 --> 06:41.809
You're drenched. Come on,
you'll catch your death.

06:46.990 --> 06:49.925
I thought you were going
to miss dinner again.

06:50.127 --> 06:53.460
Ladies have better things to do
than poison their minds with books.

06:53.664 --> 06:54.392
Such as?

06:54.898 --> 06:57.230
Such as minding their manners.

06:57.434 --> 06:59.402
The butcher said he must be paid.

06:59.636 --> 07:01.331
Sera, do you know when you sail?

07:01.538 --> 07:02.732
Next week.

07:02.906 --> 07:04.635
Wish I could sail the high seas.

07:05.075 --> 07:07.236
Veronica, high seas, indeed.

07:08.211 --> 07:10.907
She'll never find a husband
if she carries on like a child.

07:14.551 --> 07:16.849
How do people marry, Mother?

07:17.921 --> 07:19.616
They strike a bargain.

07:20.757 --> 07:22.725
What's to bargain over
if you're in love?

07:23.026 --> 07:26.223
Marriage is a contract,
not a perpetual tryst.

07:26.496 --> 07:28.555
Have you got someone in mind?

07:37.641 --> 07:39.700
- Love poetry?
- Give it back!

07:39.876 --> 07:41.901
"Life's harshness all forgave

07:42.112 --> 07:44.478
Hearts yearning met
When God...

07:45.248 --> 07:46.476
...your soul did..."

07:51.955 --> 07:53.752
Must be true love.

07:57.894 --> 07:59.953
I'd have made a dashing courtier.

08:01.965 --> 08:03.865
Or maybe a pirate!

08:06.036 --> 08:06.798
Disengage.

08:07.137 --> 08:10.334
And again, back.
Back, extend and lunge.

08:16.079 --> 08:17.671
<i>Nor in hope</i>

08:18.548 --> 08:20.948
<i>The world can show a fatal...</i>

08:21.218 --> 08:23.186
<i>... love for me</i>

08:23.420 --> 08:25.445
<i>But since that I must...</i>

08:25.689 --> 08:29.989
<i>I really love you
Please won't you love me</i>

08:45.609 --> 08:47.474
And where might you be going?

08:48.779 --> 08:49.939
Nowhere.

08:50.947 --> 08:53.313
That 'nowhere' has a nice tenor.

09:08.432 --> 09:11.560
Veronica is on the canal
with Marco Venier. Alone.

09:12.569 --> 09:14.161
Mother Franco!

09:14.404 --> 09:18.170
Elena, don't call me that.
Makes me feel ancient.

09:18.408 --> 09:21.673
Young ladies of marriageable age
must be chaperoned.

09:21.912 --> 09:25.006
A good marriage for Veronica
could win me a proper commission.

09:25.215 --> 09:26.477
I always liked Marco.

09:26.750 --> 09:28.547
He won't marry her
if he's had her.

09:28.752 --> 09:32.244
Marry her? A bride of Marco's
will need a king's ransom.

09:36.726 --> 09:40.218
"I see my fated stars
Your eyes...

09:41.098 --> 09:44.192
They melt me as the sun does snow"

09:50.006 --> 09:51.837
I bought this in Rome for you.

09:55.445 --> 09:56.776
You didn't buy it for me.

09:56.980 --> 09:58.038
Yes, I did.

09:58.381 --> 09:59.473
I just didn't know it.

10:04.054 --> 10:06.852
Such an easy gift might easily
be taken back again.

10:09.559 --> 10:11.527
Then name me any other gift.

10:12.929 --> 10:14.590
The book will do for now.

10:15.966 --> 10:18.093
I think perhaps you're too young...

10:18.535 --> 10:20.196
...to accept what I would...

10:20.437 --> 10:21.597
...truly give you.

10:22.606 --> 10:26.474
I am not so young
as you are vain.

10:28.245 --> 10:29.803
You haven't changed, have you?

10:31.615 --> 10:32.809
How would you know?

10:46.563 --> 10:50.192
I fear you mistake me for
one of your easy court companions.

10:55.572 --> 10:57.836
I mistook the asking in your eyes.

11:13.890 --> 11:15.380
Do you not like my kiss?

11:17.594 --> 11:20.358
I wish it were not a sin
to have liked it so.

11:20.764 --> 11:22.527
God made sin...

11:22.732 --> 11:25.292
...that we might know His mercy.

11:58.401 --> 12:00.961
<i>I find myself within his eyes</i>

12:02.172 --> 12:04.663
<i>I long for more of myself to know</i>

12:05.575 --> 12:08.009
<i>He hears, it seems, my silent cries</i>

12:08.712 --> 12:11.340
<i>And makes my heart my reason's foe</i>

12:12.949 --> 12:15.918
<i>How can this be, to love so quickly?</i>

12:16.553 --> 12:18.987
<i>"Love does not wait," is his reply</i>

12:20.190 --> 12:22.784
<i>What magic weaves
his touch to trick me?</i>

12:24.194 --> 12:26.685
<i>How can I now my love deny?</i>

12:36.873 --> 12:38.340
For my bride...

12:38.575 --> 12:41.305
...a little wedding trinket.

12:54.190 --> 12:57.353
Lorenzo Gritti and his fair bride

12:57.761 --> 13:00.389
Your union gives us greatest pride

13:01.064 --> 13:04.397
Good health, great wealth
and lasting line

13:21.351 --> 13:23.581
- How could they?
- How could who what?

13:23.753 --> 13:27.018
Your parents marry your sister off
to that piece of decaying flesh.

13:27.223 --> 13:31.990
That piece of decaying flesh is a cousin
of the doge, confidant of the pope.

13:32.195 --> 13:35.494
- The Roman court adores him.
- They don't have to sleep with him.

13:35.732 --> 13:36.994
You'd be surprised.

13:37.200 --> 13:42.103
Save your blushes. They don't sit well
with the bluntness of your tongue.

13:42.639 --> 13:47.008
Surely they could have traded down
a few ducats for an ounce of virility.

13:47.077 --> 13:48.738
- Why?
- For your sister's sake.

13:48.912 --> 13:49.879
She's a prude.

13:50.080 --> 13:53.447
Then it would hardly have been
more cruel marrying her to God.

13:53.683 --> 13:56.117
God isn't as rich as Lorenzo Gritti.

14:02.625 --> 14:05.992
Do honor to the houses
of Gritti and Venier.

14:06.429 --> 14:07.896
For Venice.

14:32.389 --> 14:36.018
I've seen how you look at her,
how she looks at you. I know that look.

14:36.659 --> 14:39.492
Do not underestimate
love's allure, Marco.

14:39.796 --> 14:42.026
Enjoy it...

14:42.665 --> 14:45.225
...but guard your head and your heart.

14:46.469 --> 14:47.902
You cannot marry her.

14:48.438 --> 14:49.564
I know.

14:51.741 --> 14:52.901
Pietro, come.

15:11.261 --> 15:13.320
I wish that were our bridal chamber.

15:24.007 --> 15:26.601
You think me terribly wicked
for saying that?

15:32.182 --> 15:34.013
You know we can't marry.

15:38.021 --> 15:39.955
I know only what you tell me.

15:42.192 --> 15:43.853
I must marry...

15:44.461 --> 15:48.022
...according to my station
and my family's wealth.

15:50.867 --> 15:52.061
Then why are you here?

15:53.203 --> 15:54.864
Because I could not stay away.

15:55.138 --> 15:56.503
Then don't.

15:59.976 --> 16:03.434
My marriage must be a marriage of state.

16:07.150 --> 16:09.914
My people are true citizens
700 years back.

16:10.753 --> 16:13.187
A coat of arms does not
an inheritance make.

16:14.757 --> 16:16.691
I speak of love and you talk of money.

16:16.893 --> 16:17.860
Of my duty.

16:18.094 --> 16:19.118
And your heart?

16:19.829 --> 16:22.423
This isn't about my heart,
it's about politics.

16:27.904 --> 16:29.269
How romantic.

16:30.406 --> 16:33.341
Marriage isn't romantic.
That's why God invented poetry.

16:33.543 --> 16:35.374
To sweeten men's lying lips!

16:35.578 --> 16:37.910
If I were a liar,
would I tell you this now?

16:38.114 --> 16:40.605
If you cared for me,
you could not tell me this ever.

16:42.619 --> 16:44.086
I want you.

16:48.391 --> 16:49.915
Not enough.

17:09.145 --> 17:11.409
Daughter, you have reached too high.

17:12.148 --> 17:14.742
I told you, marriage is a contract.

17:17.320 --> 17:21.086
To a man of Marco's station,
it has nothing to do with love.

17:23.159 --> 17:25.423
But you can still have Marco.

17:29.599 --> 17:31.260
But not in wedlock.

17:36.940 --> 17:39.272
There's an alternative to marriage.

17:42.178 --> 17:43.611
You'll become a courtesan.

17:47.283 --> 17:51.185
I've seen you watching them.
I've seen you mesmerized by them.

17:53.957 --> 17:56.016
You'll become a courtesan...

17:58.528 --> 18:00.155
...like your mother used to be.

18:11.040 --> 18:12.473
You were a courtesan?

18:13.476 --> 18:14.738
One of the best.

18:18.581 --> 18:19.309
When?

18:20.550 --> 18:22.017
A long time ago.

18:25.221 --> 18:28.884
I had hoped to buy you a good marriage.

18:29.392 --> 18:30.950
But your father...

18:31.494 --> 18:33.519
...drank away your dowry.

18:33.896 --> 18:35.659
Your brother must buy his posting.

18:36.065 --> 18:37.828
And I am too old.

18:38.801 --> 18:39.597
It is you...

18:40.169 --> 18:42.228
...who must support us now.

18:44.741 --> 18:45.799
Look at these hands.

18:46.476 --> 18:47.704
Soft.

18:49.245 --> 18:50.337
Too soft...

18:50.546 --> 18:52.138
...for a scullery maid...

18:52.348 --> 18:54.077
...or working the winery.

18:54.484 --> 18:56.349
Perhaps a lady's maid.

18:59.255 --> 19:02.520
- Wouldn't that be funny?
- Send me to the convent then!

19:02.725 --> 19:04.192
You are not the type.

19:04.427 --> 19:05.860
How would you know?

19:10.833 --> 19:11.800
What're you doing?

19:12.602 --> 19:16.231
Whichever devil you choose,
you'll look him in the eye first...

19:16.439 --> 19:18.407
...which is more than my mother gave me.

19:57.780 --> 20:01.147
First secret of all great courtesans:

20:02.485 --> 20:04.453
You must know pleasure...

20:04.687 --> 20:06.211
...to give pleasure.

20:07.590 --> 20:10.423
Beauty is a manifestation of the divine.

20:10.626 --> 20:14.062
That theory built the Sistine Chapel,
and it'll do the same for you.

20:16.299 --> 20:19.200
Height is an advantage to women
as well as men.

20:19.836 --> 20:22.134
Carriage creates the first impression.

21:27.703 --> 21:29.136
Come with me, Veronica.

21:33.376 --> 21:35.310
Mother, we can't go in there.

21:35.511 --> 21:37.274
Ladies can't go in there.

21:38.247 --> 21:39.874
Courtesans can.

21:50.893 --> 21:54.488
The emperor Pericles relied
more for policy on his mistress...

21:54.697 --> 21:56.927
...than he ever did on his lieutenants.

21:57.600 --> 22:01.900
Courtesans, my dear, are the
most educated women in the world.

22:33.035 --> 22:36.402
<i>A courtesan is a force of nature
in a civilized cloak.</i>

22:36.706 --> 22:39.436
<i>Any chambermaid can flop down,
take off her shirt...</i>

22:39.642 --> 22:40.768
<i>... and men will come.</i>

22:40.943 --> 22:45.312
Your true power comes from
something much deeper than beauty.

22:46.215 --> 22:47.614
Cleopatra knew that.

22:48.084 --> 22:49.346
Theodosia.

22:49.552 --> 22:52.646
Aspasia.
She could seduce a man at 20 paces...

22:52.822 --> 22:55.188
...without revealing an inch of flesh.

22:56.292 --> 22:57.156
How?

22:57.460 --> 22:58.825
With her mind.

22:59.462 --> 23:00.952
Desire begins in the mind.

23:02.365 --> 23:03.798
I don't understand.

23:05.534 --> 23:06.501
No, you don't.

23:09.372 --> 23:10.498
Think of Marco.

23:13.676 --> 23:15.303
I know you know anger.

23:17.613 --> 23:18.841
Try disdain.

23:26.622 --> 23:27.589
Amusement.

23:32.662 --> 23:33.629
Submission.

23:41.637 --> 23:42.604
Rapture.

23:54.884 --> 23:55.851
Now...

23:57.553 --> 24:01.011
...make him believe that he is
the only man in the universe.

24:21.043 --> 24:22.237
Who taught you?

24:22.745 --> 24:24.144
Your grandmother.

24:31.520 --> 24:34.956
In order to choose your lovers wisely,
you need to understand men.

24:36.826 --> 24:39.056
No matter their shape or size...

24:40.363 --> 24:41.796
...position or wealth...

24:43.699 --> 24:44.825
...they all dream...

24:45.034 --> 24:46.365
...of the temptress.

24:49.538 --> 24:50.869
The irresistible...

24:51.073 --> 24:53.371
...unapproachable Venus...

24:54.377 --> 24:57.744
...who quickly turns pliable maiden
when they've had a hard day.

25:48.798 --> 25:49.765
Come.

25:49.965 --> 25:51.762
You can't be squeamish.

25:54.603 --> 25:56.332
If you don't enjoy it...

25:56.806 --> 25:59.502
...they'll smell it,
like a dog smells fear.

26:00.609 --> 26:02.338
And they'll hate you for it.

26:04.814 --> 26:07.146
What's there to be squeamish about?

26:17.460 --> 26:18.757
If you touch...

26:18.994 --> 26:20.086
...here.

26:23.833 --> 26:25.232
Amazing.

26:25.468 --> 26:26.867
Use your fingers lightly...

26:27.069 --> 26:28.536
...like feathers.

26:31.006 --> 26:33.770
Your tongue, like licking sweets.

26:34.477 --> 26:36.445
Your teeth, with restraint.

26:38.013 --> 26:39.708
Just enough...

26:41.183 --> 26:43.151
...to keep him wanting more.

26:43.853 --> 26:45.320
It's wanting...

26:45.855 --> 26:47.550
...that keeps us alive.

27:54.557 --> 27:56.184
Minister Ramberti.

27:56.859 --> 27:59.589
I'd like to present you
to my daughter, Veronica.

28:01.363 --> 28:03.763
It would bring me luck if you'd
play a hand for me.

28:06.635 --> 28:09.229
Remember, Veronica, love love.

28:09.471 --> 28:11.996
But do not love the man,
or you'll be in his power.

28:12.208 --> 28:13.573
Good luck.

28:20.115 --> 28:21.605
May I call?

28:22.384 --> 28:23.851
May I call?

28:29.792 --> 28:31.054
Lovely.

28:40.402 --> 28:42.563
This is my first bet.

28:42.738 --> 28:44.262
Your first?

28:45.074 --> 28:46.974
Unmistakably.

28:48.811 --> 28:50.142
I'm honored.

28:53.882 --> 28:55.816
Repent your empty excesses!

28:56.252 --> 28:58.117
There is no comfort here.

29:07.529 --> 29:08.655
Friends.

29:08.831 --> 29:11.459
May I ask you, is this God's game?

29:11.700 --> 29:13.668
Why do you gamble with your souls?

29:13.836 --> 29:15.167
What is it you want?

29:15.537 --> 29:17.095
Your salvation.

29:19.108 --> 29:21.269
This is no company for one so fair.

29:41.630 --> 29:44.758
Venice may as well be deemed
one large floating brothel.

29:44.967 --> 29:47.936
What's biting your ass
this fair evening, cousin?

29:50.372 --> 29:53.830
You'd begrudge the fairer sex
their little crumbs?

29:54.310 --> 29:58.144
No, though they do make more
in a night than I a month.

29:58.580 --> 30:00.707
Go make yourself useful.
Give us a rhyme.

30:00.883 --> 30:03.443
I'm no performing monkey
for the idle masses.

30:03.686 --> 30:04.983
Since when?

30:05.187 --> 30:08.054
We're all of us
performing monkeys, nephew.

30:08.424 --> 30:09.891
Paupers and poets alike.

30:12.227 --> 30:13.751
I'm at your service, Uncle.

30:14.363 --> 30:16.695
If it's rhyme you wish,
I'll gladly oblige.

30:20.235 --> 30:21.031
A subject?

30:21.837 --> 30:22.531
Doge?

30:25.541 --> 30:28.203
Venice. To celebrate our plenty.

30:31.013 --> 30:32.708
Born in glory

30:33.248 --> 30:35.910
The virgin's exultation

30:36.652 --> 30:38.745
Fair and mighty Venice

30:39.254 --> 30:40.380
Queen of the sea

30:40.756 --> 30:42.724
Unconquered maid

30:43.025 --> 30:45.255
Sovereign isle is she

30:50.933 --> 30:52.161
Chaste goddess

30:52.368 --> 30:54.928
Rising from the foamy depths

30:57.740 --> 30:58.707
Wine?

30:58.941 --> 31:00.101
Please.

31:23.265 --> 31:25.893
<i>Signor Venier? Don't be absurd.</i>

31:26.235 --> 31:28.066
I'm not being absurd.
I'm just...

31:28.303 --> 31:30.737
...treating you with indifference,
as you did me.

31:30.906 --> 31:33.739
You confuse indifference with honesty.

31:33.909 --> 31:35.740
You confuse honesty with venality.

31:35.911 --> 31:37.879
You think me venal?

31:38.213 --> 31:40.408
You are a venal cur.

31:42.317 --> 31:43.579
Hello, Marco.

31:43.786 --> 31:45.413
Something I can do for you?

31:56.598 --> 32:00.056
Here, beauty, wit and wealth combined

32:01.770 --> 32:04.261
Gateway 'twixt distant East and West

32:04.706 --> 32:06.139
Mother of liberty

32:06.341 --> 32:07.467
Child of honor

32:07.709 --> 32:10.303
Home and hearth and heart

32:10.512 --> 32:12.946
To men of valor

32:24.259 --> 32:27.422
Perhaps the fair maiden can do better.

32:35.037 --> 32:36.004
A duel!

33:02.498 --> 33:03.829
Venice...

33:04.399 --> 33:05.491
...mother...

33:06.568 --> 33:08.399
...virgin, queen and...

33:09.171 --> 33:10.331
...goddess

33:12.407 --> 33:14.875
To be all 5 at once is no mean trick.

33:17.279 --> 33:20.715
If women's lust lost Eden
Our redress to be

33:21.383 --> 33:25.114
Hearth, heart and home to every...

33:26.455 --> 33:27.183
...prick.

33:31.793 --> 33:32.657
Who is she?

33:39.968 --> 33:41.435
Sweet lagoon

33:42.237 --> 33:43.966
That brings us...

33:44.306 --> 33:45.739
...Iovely life

33:52.581 --> 33:54.310
Rank with...

33:54.650 --> 33:57.278
...greed and trade's...

33:59.254 --> 34:00.915
