1:12:59.025 --> 1:13:00.185
Your tears.

1:13:03.029 --> 1:13:04.894
You yearn for my tears?

1:13:11.671 --> 1:13:12.899
I don't think so.

1:13:18.177 --> 1:13:19.508
Then what do I yearn for?

1:14:03.289 --> 1:14:05.257
Why don't we find out?

1:15:00.613 --> 1:15:01.773
You'll get your ships.

1:15:13.159 --> 1:15:15.423
- Poet to kings.
- A national asset.

1:15:15.628 --> 1:15:17.289
More than 100 French ships.

1:15:17.530 --> 1:15:19.828
We should make you
ambassador to the emperor.

1:15:20.533 --> 1:15:21.966
He doesn't deserve her.

1:15:26.706 --> 1:15:29.140
Would he sooner we didn't get the ships?

1:15:29.375 --> 1:15:32.776
He would rather he had the right
to refuse even a king your hand.

1:15:43.956 --> 1:15:45.446
I could not refuse.

1:15:45.658 --> 1:15:46.682
Couldn't you?

1:15:47.193 --> 1:15:48.660
I think you like it.

1:15:49.028 --> 1:15:50.655
You like what it has made me.

1:15:54.867 --> 1:15:56.801
I don't like what it makes me.

1:15:57.336 --> 1:15:58.735
Why did you not stop me?

1:16:00.506 --> 1:16:01.803
You're not mine to stop!

1:16:02.041 --> 1:16:03.372
Whose fault is that?

1:16:06.679 --> 1:16:08.772
You sleep with Giulia for duty's sake.

1:16:09.348 --> 1:16:12.749
I slept with the IKing of France once for
duty's sake. Who does not forgive?

1:16:14.353 --> 1:16:15.752
Perhaps I can't live with it.

1:16:32.071 --> 1:16:33.595
I pray God to watch over you.

1:16:34.173 --> 1:16:36.539
Save your prayers, Veronica.

1:16:37.176 --> 1:16:40.805
The devil's got my heart now.
God hasn't a chance.

1:17:45.711 --> 1:17:48.612
We were hoping you'd tell us
what's happening with the war.

1:18:00.726 --> 1:18:02.023
What do you know?

1:18:03.196 --> 1:18:05.460
Just that we're
fighting the Turks again.

1:18:08.935 --> 1:18:10.266
And that's all?

1:18:14.040 --> 1:18:16.907
Their sultan sent us an ultimatum.

1:18:17.109 --> 1:18:21.375
Either we surrender Cyprus or he takes it
by force. Our fleets went to defend it.

1:18:21.614 --> 1:18:24.583
Is Cyprus so important,
we must send our husbands to battle?

1:18:25.218 --> 1:18:26.549
Without Cyprus...

1:18:26.752 --> 1:18:29.186
...we lose control over
the eastern Mediterranean.

1:18:33.659 --> 1:18:35.217
I know we own it...

1:18:35.494 --> 1:18:37.428
...but where exactly is Cyprus?

1:18:37.763 --> 1:18:38.957
My husband...

1:18:39.298 --> 1:18:41.766
...do you know if he is alive or dead?

1:18:43.302 --> 1:18:44.792
Alive and well.

1:18:46.706 --> 1:18:47.673
And mine?

1:18:49.242 --> 1:18:51.676
The admiral is alive. And a hero.

1:18:55.915 --> 1:18:57.109
And my husband?

1:18:57.617 --> 1:18:58.709
Who is your husband?

1:18:58.951 --> 1:18:59.747
Vicco.

1:18:59.952 --> 1:19:01.749
My husband is Pietro Vicco.

1:19:01.921 --> 1:19:03.946
He's strong. He'll come home safely.

1:19:06.926 --> 1:19:08.359
You know her husband well.

1:19:12.698 --> 1:19:15.223
Not at all well,
but his reputation precedes him.

1:19:17.270 --> 1:19:18.328
Go on, ask her.

1:19:20.006 --> 1:19:21.974
Ask her what you're longing to.

1:19:23.809 --> 1:19:28.542
Ask her what draws our husbands
back to her again and again...

1:19:30.049 --> 1:19:31.448
...like pigs to a trough!

1:19:41.460 --> 1:19:44.088
<i>The Latin for banana is ariena.</i>

1:19:46.766 --> 1:19:48.734
<i>Banana tree is pala.</i>

1:20:11.157 --> 1:20:14.786
A woman's greatest
and most hard-won asset...

1:20:15.494 --> 1:20:16.927
...is an education.

1:20:18.331 --> 1:20:22.529
Just because you can say it in Latin
doesn't make it less obscene.

1:20:22.768 --> 1:20:25.396
Just because you took a vow
doesn't mean you know love.

1:20:29.408 --> 1:20:34.004
Either that whore leaves or I leave.
No Christian woman could tolerate this!

1:20:34.246 --> 1:20:36.077
You're unfit to be a mother.

1:20:37.750 --> 1:20:39.718
At least I am a mother.

1:20:45.758 --> 1:20:48.192
<i>Thank you for your assistance,
Signora Franco.</i>

1:21:02.742 --> 1:21:04.039
He's alive.

1:21:12.218 --> 1:21:13.685
You made many enemies today.

1:21:14.053 --> 1:21:15.418
They were already enemies.

1:21:15.654 --> 1:21:17.383
Now they will become more so.

1:21:19.125 --> 1:21:20.922
Did you come to warn me?

1:21:30.736 --> 1:21:32.135
...make her a courtesan.

1:21:35.408 --> 1:21:36.898
I will not pimp your daughter.

1:21:37.143 --> 1:21:39.111
Look at the life you live.

1:21:39.812 --> 1:21:41.541
The freedom that you have.

1:21:41.747 --> 1:21:43.612
You'll deny my daughter
the same chance?

1:21:47.086 --> 1:21:48.348
Turn right up ahead.

1:21:53.459 --> 1:21:54.426
Look.

1:21:55.594 --> 1:21:56.993
Look outside.

1:22:05.004 --> 1:22:06.972
This is where we go to die.

1:22:07.940 --> 1:22:09.908
You will not end here.

1:22:12.878 --> 1:22:15.176
Livia, Venice's reigning Venus.

1:22:16.715 --> 1:22:18.512
A jealous lover did that.

1:22:21.787 --> 1:22:23.254
Who wants her now?

1:22:26.125 --> 1:22:28.593
My cage seems bigger than yours,
but it's still a cage.

1:22:28.828 --> 1:22:30.557
You won't get sympathy from me.

1:22:30.796 --> 1:22:31.956
I don't want it.

1:22:32.198 --> 1:22:35.998
Do you know what my
daughter's nurse told her today?

1:22:37.670 --> 1:22:40.161
That in a girl's voice lies temptation.

1:22:41.941 --> 1:22:46.810
A known fact. Eloquence in a woman
means promiscuity.

1:22:47.646 --> 1:22:48.943
Promiscuity of the mind...

1:22:49.148 --> 1:22:51.981
...leads to promiscuity of the body.

1:22:53.986 --> 1:22:56.614
She doesn't believe her yet,
but she will.

1:22:57.056 --> 1:22:58.546
She'll grow up like her mother.

1:22:59.492 --> 1:23:02.359
She'll marry, bear children...

1:23:02.561 --> 1:23:06.361
...and honor her family.
Spend her youth in needlepoint...

1:23:09.335 --> 1:23:10.825
And when she dies...

1:23:11.170 --> 1:23:14.833
...she'll wonder why she obeyed
all the rules of God and country...

1:23:15.074 --> 1:23:17.975
...because no biblical hell
could ever be worse...

1:23:18.177 --> 1:23:20.907
...than this state
of perpetual inconsequence.

1:23:29.388 --> 1:23:32.084
<i>Silent God ignores my prayer</i>

1:23:32.625 --> 1:23:34.024
<i>And renders lost</i>

1:23:34.226 --> 1:23:36.057
<i>What once was fair</i>

1:23:37.229 --> 1:23:40.255
<i>Once blissful
Fortune's favorite city</i>

1:23:41.634 --> 1:23:43.261
<i>Now wheeled fate turns</i>

1:23:44.470 --> 1:23:46.233
<i>No trace of pity</i>

1:23:56.148 --> 1:23:58.582
<i>Citizens of Venice!</i>

1:23:58.817 --> 1:24:02.514
<i>Look around you now
at the disease and deaths...</i>

1:24:02.755 --> 1:24:07.158
<i>... that have taken over
our once beautiful city, and tell me...</i>

1:24:07.660 --> 1:24:10.185
<i>... this plague is not a punishment...</i>

1:24:10.429 --> 1:24:11.828
<i>... from God!</i>

1:24:12.765 --> 1:24:16.064
<i>We are surrounded by harlots...</i>

1:24:16.268 --> 1:24:17.735
<i>... and courtesans!</i>

1:24:18.003 --> 1:24:21.336
<i>We must cast out
those who tempt us...</i>

1:24:21.607 --> 1:24:24.235
...for we are a city of shame...

1:24:25.177 --> 1:24:26.735
<i>... of fornication...</i>

1:24:27.012 --> 1:24:30.743
<i>... and carnal practices
that defy description.</i>

1:24:32.184 --> 1:24:35.745
<i>We will go the way of Sodom
and Gomorrah...</i>

1:24:36.288 --> 1:24:39.348
<i>... and become dust
in the sands of time!</i>

1:24:47.633 --> 1:24:49.794
There's news from Venice.

1:25:23.569 --> 1:25:26.333
The corruption of flesh,
the paint on their faces...

1:25:27.239 --> 1:25:31.175
...the vile coloring of their hair,
their wanton dress...

1:25:31.510 --> 1:25:33.535
Look on them and within yourselves.

1:26:21.760 --> 1:26:23.125
You're alive.

1:26:23.862 --> 1:26:25.295
You're alive.

1:26:36.241 --> 1:26:37.606
Forgive me.

1:27:00.766 --> 1:27:02.290
Please forgive me.

1:27:13.445 --> 1:27:14.639
I'm sorry.

1:28:04.963 --> 1:28:06.931
<i>Signora Veronica Franco...</i>

1:28:07.166 --> 1:28:11.865
...I hereby summon you to appear before
the tribunal of the Holy Inquisition.

1:28:13.906 --> 1:28:17.364
You have no jurisdiction here, Senator.
I speak for the Church.

1:28:33.125 --> 1:28:34.592
The Inquisition?

1:28:35.394 --> 1:28:36.361
In Venice?

1:28:36.562 --> 1:28:37.995
We have 56,000 dead.

1:28:39.231 --> 1:28:42.826
The living want answers. They may be
wrong answers, but they want them.

1:28:43.101 --> 1:28:45.194
Be glad the bastards
aren't burning us out.

1:28:45.437 --> 1:28:46.563
You can stop it!

1:28:48.106 --> 1:28:51.542
If the doge came out in defense
of a notorious courtesan...

1:28:51.743 --> 1:28:55.804
Now she's notorious?
Before she was a national asset.

1:28:56.215 --> 1:28:57.978
It would topple the government.

1:28:58.217 --> 1:29:00.048
These are grim times, Senator.

1:29:03.722 --> 1:29:05.314
You're an elected official.

1:29:05.557 --> 1:29:07.457
You cannot refuse your office.

1:29:08.160 --> 1:29:11.129
Then you compel me
to condone these proceedings.

1:29:11.330 --> 1:29:13.764
Am I mistaken, or is Venice
still a free republic?

1:30:51.330 --> 1:30:54.493
By order of the pope, the Inquisition
has come to Venice...

1:30:54.733 --> 1:30:58.567
...to seek out heresy and beliefs
anathema to the Church.

1:30:59.871 --> 1:31:01.361
Veronica Franco...

1:31:02.674 --> 1:31:03.936
...you have been denounced...

1:31:04.142 --> 1:31:08.602
...on the charge of witchcraft,
a mortal sin punishable by death.

1:31:10.048 --> 1:31:13.484
Should you confess and repent
during these proceedings...

1:31:13.685 --> 1:31:18.054
...you will be mercifully welcomed back
into the bosom of the Holy Church.

1:31:21.159 --> 1:31:22.717
Your Holiness...

1:31:22.961 --> 1:31:23.928
Silence!

1:31:25.998 --> 1:31:30.765
The accused shall make no utterance but
to answer our questions or to confess.

1:31:31.436 --> 1:31:32.767
Proceed, Monsignor.

1:31:41.013 --> 1:31:42.037
Venice...

1:31:43.515 --> 1:31:45.449
...ever a noble republic...

1:31:46.018 --> 1:31:47.576
...home of learning...

1:31:48.286 --> 1:31:50.811
...art, commerce...

1:31:51.757 --> 1:31:54.726
...has been brought low
by war and plague.

1:31:55.761 --> 1:31:57.353
Do you know why?

1:31:57.929 --> 1:31:59.863
I am not that wise.

1:32:00.298 --> 1:32:01.230
Tell us...

1:32:01.466 --> 1:32:02.694
...how many...

1:32:03.101 --> 1:32:06.400
...of the worthy men of this city
have you taken into your chamber?

1:32:08.573 --> 1:32:09.938
I've not counted my lovers.

1:32:16.048 --> 1:32:17.174
Answer the question.

1:32:18.784 --> 1:32:19.478
Yes.

1:32:20.052 --> 1:32:21.019
More than 100?

1:32:21.253 --> 1:32:22.117
I don't know.

1:32:22.354 --> 1:32:23.218
You don't?

1:32:23.455 --> 1:32:26.982
Yet for each you paraded your
milky breast and hair of spun copper.

1:32:27.225 --> 1:32:29.625
For each you learned his
unique favored touch...

1:32:29.795 --> 1:32:32.525
...and enchanted him to believe
he was the only man in the universe.

1:32:32.764 --> 1:32:34.095
How many per week?

1:32:35.133 --> 1:32:37.192
I told you. I enchanted no one.

1:32:37.469 --> 1:32:41.735
Did you feign love with more than 10
weekly? Or would 5 or 6 have sated you?

1:32:41.907 --> 1:32:42.999
I never feigned love.

1:32:43.241 --> 1:32:44.173
So why'd they pay?

1:32:46.745 --> 1:32:47.973
For the dream of love...

1:32:49.681 --> 1:32:52.980
...as it cannot exist in this world
that you've created.

1:32:54.086 --> 1:32:57.487
For the hope there might exist
on earth some corner of this paradise...

1:32:57.689 --> 1:32:58.986
Paradise?

1:32:59.758 --> 1:33:01.350
When 56,000 have fallen?

1:33:01.693 --> 1:33:02.717
You say this.

1:33:02.928 --> 1:33:03.895
You...

1:33:04.529 --> 1:33:07.726
...who fill your home with feast
and dance while Venice suffers?

1:33:07.933 --> 1:33:10.424
Who creates a sumptuous
world of flesh...

1:33:10.635 --> 1:33:13.536
...and depravity, of orgiastic rites
invoking the devil?

1:33:13.738 --> 1:33:16.172
- This is paradise?
- The only devilry here is your spite!

1:33:16.875 --> 1:33:18.672
He's jealous of what he cannot have!

1:33:18.844 --> 1:33:20.812
Do not intrude into the proceedings.

1:33:21.012 --> 1:33:24.243
I'm a senator of Venice.
The Inquisition is here by our consent.

1:33:24.483 --> 1:33:28.044
This is an ecclesiastical court.
You are here by my consent.

1:33:28.286 --> 1:33:29.878
This is a personal vendetta.

1:33:30.122 --> 1:33:32.488
You will abide by our rules
or be removed.

1:33:32.691 --> 1:33:34.022
Is that understood?

1:33:35.560 --> 1:33:37.391
Is that understood?

1:33:46.671 --> 1:33:48.696
The senator speaks the truth.

1:33:49.808 --> 1:33:51.207
I was bewitched by her.

1:33:55.580 --> 1:33:59.744
In my weakness, I fell under her spell
to pathetic ruin.

1:33:59.985 --> 1:34:02.647
It's only by the grace of God
I stand here today.

1:34:03.421 --> 1:34:04.547
I didn't seek your love.

1:34:04.756 --> 1:34:07.281
Because I could not pay your fee.

1:34:08.059 --> 1:34:09.219
I loved another.

1:34:09.594 --> 1:34:10.856
In other words...

1:34:11.062 --> 1:34:13.929
...you cast your spell over all
who cross your path.

1:34:14.166 --> 1:34:19.069
You compel sacred love to garner riches.
What is this if not witchcraft?

1:34:20.038 --> 1:34:22.165
Ever give yourself to a man
who couldn't pay?

1:34:22.440 --> 1:34:24.738
I gave my heart where
riches were no use.

1:34:24.910 --> 1:34:26.377
I did what was needed to live.

1:34:26.611 --> 1:34:29.045
Did you give yourself
to a man who could not pay?

1:34:29.247 --> 1:34:33.843
What other profession do you allow me?
How shall I survive if I cannot marry?

1:34:34.085 --> 1:34:35.143
Answer!

1:34:35.387 --> 1:34:37.855
Why, when you are determined to damn me?

1:34:40.091 --> 1:34:41.149
Look at her.

1:34:42.260 --> 1:34:43.227
Feel her wrath...

1:34:45.864 --> 1:34:50.301
She, who lures the noble fathers
of Venice from their wives...

1:34:50.569 --> 1:34:51.729
...their children...

1:34:52.370 --> 1:34:54.201
...their ability to lead the republic!

1:34:54.573 --> 1:34:58.532
It is she and her kind who turned
God's hands against us, Your Grace.

1:34:58.777 --> 1:35:00.108
Your Grace...

1:35:00.579 --> 1:35:01.705
...we must do our duty.

1:35:03.215 --> 1:35:07.345
Veronica Franco, you hover at the brink
of extermination and hell.

1:35:08.053 --> 1:35:12.251
You will return tomorrow to hear God's
merciful judgment and, I hope...

1:35:13.124 --> 1:35:16.582
...to repent before that judgment
takes its course.

1:35:17.329 --> 1:35:18.796
Remove the prisoner.

1:35:59.304 --> 1:36:00.703
You must save yourself.

1:36:01.773 --> 1:36:02.637
How?

1:36:02.974 --> 1:36:06.068
Confess whatever foolishness
they put before you...

1:36:06.611 --> 1:36:07.578
That I'm a witch?

1:36:07.746 --> 1:36:09.270
What does it matter what you say?

1:36:09.547 --> 1:36:11.412
I would be saying it.

1:36:12.183 --> 1:36:14.811
There is no honor with fools like these.

1:36:15.320 --> 1:36:16.651
God will forgive you.

1:36:18.623 --> 1:36:21.717
If I give them my lie,
I give them my soul.

1:36:22.327 --> 1:36:24.761
I'll lose everything I ever was.

1:36:25.330 --> 1:36:27.230
My love, my words, my heart.

1:36:27.432 --> 1:36:28.490
But you would live.

1:36:30.001 --> 1:36:31.593
As someone else.

1:36:32.003 --> 1:36:34.972
I've let you go too many times.

1:36:35.774 --> 1:36:37.002
I can't do it again.

1:36:38.843 --> 1:36:40.640
There is no choice.

1:36:50.021 --> 1:36:51.386
I'll never see you again.

1:37:27.759 --> 1:37:31.525
Veronica Franco, you have been
denounced a sorceress.

1:37:32.697 --> 1:37:36.997
Either confess and plead mercy,
or stand to receive my judgment.

1:37:39.170 --> 1:37:40.797
I will confess, Your Grace.

1:37:47.579 --> 1:37:49.706
That will please God.

1:37:50.248 --> 1:37:51.078
Proceed.

1:37:52.917 --> 1:37:54.384
I confess...

1:37:54.586 --> 1:37:58.352
...as a girl I loved a man who would not
marry me for want of a dowry.

1:37:59.724 --> 1:38:03.091
I confess I had a mother
who taught me a different way of life.

1:38:03.762 --> 1:38:06.128
One I resisted at first
but learned to embrace.

1:38:07.098 --> 1:38:09.566
I confess I became a courtesan.

1:38:09.768 --> 1:38:13.704
Traded yearning for power, welcomed many
rather than be owned by one.

1:38:13.872 --> 1:38:15.737
She does not speak to the charge.

1:38:15.907 --> 1:38:20.037
I confess I embraced a whore's freedom
over a wife's obedience.

1:38:20.278 --> 1:38:22.246
This is not repentance.

1:38:22.947 --> 1:38:24.414
What am I to do?

1:38:24.682 --> 1:38:27.480
I must confess my evil.
These are my sins.

1:38:27.886 --> 1:38:31.083
Your Grace, her mortal sins
are not at issue.

1:38:31.389 --> 1:38:33.152
She must repent witchcraft.

1:38:33.558 --> 1:38:36.026
Perhaps she heads in that direction.

1:38:36.294 --> 1:38:37.420
You have been warned.

1:38:37.695 --> 1:38:42.189
The Church cannot deny her right to seek
God's mercy. Confession is sacrosanct.

1:38:42.801 --> 1:38:44.860
Don't instruct me on the Church's laws!

1:38:45.136 --> 1:38:49.436
Then I call upon the doge to demand
that the Inquisition abide by them.

1:38:51.142 --> 1:38:55.078
If Christian mercy is gone, then
at least Venetian justice still exists.

1:38:55.447 --> 1:38:58.280
I pray Your Grace has heard
enough of this.

1:39:01.419 --> 1:39:05.856
It does seem odd that the Holy Mother
Church would deny a sinner confession.

1:39:06.491 --> 1:39:08.823
I see no harm in hearing her.

1:39:09.761 --> 1:39:11.888
She will save or damn herself.

1:39:12.130 --> 1:39:14.621
The prisoner has already damned herself.

1:39:15.166 --> 1:39:18.966
But if it pleases the
esteemed doge of Venice...

1:39:19.170 --> 1:39:20.762
...she may continue her heresy.

1:39:26.845 --> 1:39:30.781
I confess I find more ecstasy
in passion than in prayer.

1:39:38.122 --> 1:39:39.646
I confess...

1:39:40.358 --> 1:39:42.826
I confess I pray still...

1:39:43.862 --> 1:39:46.626
...to feel the touch
of my lover's lips...

1:39:47.365 --> 1:39:49.424
...his hands upon me...

1:39:51.236 --> 1:39:52.999
...his arms enfolding me.

1:39:53.204 --> 1:39:54.296
Veronica, stop!

1:39:55.206 --> 1:39:57.106
Save yourself, please.

1:39:59.244 --> 1:40:02.213
Such surrender has been mine.

1:40:04.249 --> 1:40:08.709
I confess I hunger still
to be filled and inflamed.

1:40:09.020 --> 1:40:11.420
To melt into the dream of us...

1:40:12.357 --> 1:40:14.086
...beyond this troubled place...

1:40:16.928 --> 1:40:18.896
...to where we are not even ourselves.

1:40:19.864 --> 1:40:21.889
To know that always...

1:40:22.600 --> 1:40:24.534
...always this is mine.

1:40:25.136 --> 1:40:26.535
Your Grace...

1:40:27.038 --> 1:40:28.733
...is this necessary?

1:40:29.040 --> 1:40:30.940
She hopes to bewitch us all.

1:40:31.376 --> 1:40:35.745
If this had not been mine,
if I had lived another way...

1:40:36.114 --> 1:40:38.048
...a child to a husband's whim...

1:40:38.383 --> 1:40:41.284
...my soul hardened from lack of touch
and lack of love...

1:40:41.619 --> 1:40:43.985
...I confess such endless days
and nights...

1:40:44.188 --> 1:40:47.021
...would be punishment greater
than any you could mete out.

1:40:47.225 --> 1:40:47.919
Finished?

1:40:48.459 --> 1:40:49.858
No, Your Grace.

1:40:51.296 --> 1:40:52.524
You, all of you...

1:40:54.465 --> 1:40:59.402
...who hunger for what I give but cannot
bear to see such power in a woman...

1:41:01.306 --> 1:41:04.139
...you call God's greatest gift...

1:41:05.743 --> 1:41:07.370
...ourselves...

1:41:07.645 --> 1:41:11.081
...our yearning, our need to love,
you call it filth...

1:41:11.316 --> 1:41:12.749
...and sin and heresy...

1:41:13.017 --> 1:41:17.420
Enough. One last time before you are
condemned: Do you repent or not?

1:41:18.489 --> 1:41:22.949
I repent there was no other way
open to me. I do not repent my life.

1:41:23.194 --> 1:41:27.893
Then the Holy Inquisition has heard the
evidence against you and is satisfied.

1:41:28.566 --> 1:41:30.033
In the name of the pope...

1:41:31.269 --> 1:41:32.736
There is more to be heard.

1:41:33.705 --> 1:41:35.434
I demand the same rights of confession!

1:41:35.673 --> 1:41:36.640
You're not on trial!

1:41:36.808 --> 1:41:40.369
We're still on consecrated ground.
I confess I am her accomplice.

1:41:43.348 --> 1:41:47.876
If she is a witch, damn me. I do not
repent. I will not live without her.

1:41:53.358 --> 1:41:55.952
This is a cynical trick.
He does this to save her.

1:41:56.194 --> 1:41:57.491
She's a witch!

1:41:58.363 --> 1:42:00.456
Proven and convicted,
the devil in our midst...

1:42:00.698 --> 1:42:04.134
...and I am her accomplice!
Condemn her if you will...

1:42:04.335 --> 1:42:07.270
...but arrest me too. Arrest a senator
of Venice for witchcraft.

1:42:07.472 --> 1:42:09.440
I'll not shrink
from judging the mighty.

1:42:09.641 --> 1:42:11.666
I welcome it. I wait for the shackles.

1:42:11.909 --> 1:42:13.604
He speaks with his heart,
not his head.

1:42:14.512 --> 1:42:16.343
He's blinded by his own lust.

1:42:16.547 --> 1:42:18.811
If she's a witch,
so is every woman in Venice!

1:42:23.821 --> 1:42:25.288
Silence!

1:42:32.930 --> 1:42:34.864
We are a strange city,
Your Holiness.

1:42:36.300 --> 1:42:38.029
Perhaps accursed.

1:42:47.111 --> 1:42:49.807
And perhaps we live
in a peculiar state of grace.

1:42:51.282 --> 1:42:53.443
I am not alone...

1:42:53.951 --> 1:42:56.010
...in loving this woman...

1:42:56.287 --> 1:42:59.313
...though I love her far, far more
than they.

1:43:02.060 --> 1:43:03.186
...were many...

1:43:04.562 --> 1:43:05.961
...and proud.

1:43:06.764 --> 1:43:08.732
If we do not speak now...

1:43:10.635 --> 1:43:12.000
...if Venice...

1:43:12.203 --> 1:43:16.799
...does not stand up now and acknowledge
who she is, then we are all damned...

1:43:17.642 --> 1:43:18.734
...not before this court...

1:43:20.378 --> 1:43:21.675
...before eternity.

1:43:23.715 --> 1:43:25.808
If what he says is true...

1:43:27.218 --> 1:43:30.051
...then you must speak the names
of your accomplices.

1:43:31.789 --> 1:43:33.154
Your Grace...

1:43:34.292 --> 1:43:36.692
...the men who loved her
were under her spell.

1:43:36.861 --> 1:43:38.488
They had no volition.

1:43:38.730 --> 1:43:41.164
Shall we punish
even the victims of her evil?

1:43:42.767 --> 1:43:45.258
If the soul of the city is corrupt...

1:43:45.636 --> 1:43:48.696
...and you help me root it out,
I will spare your life.

1:43:55.947 --> 1:43:58.438
I had no accomplices, Your Grace.

1:44:03.821 --> 1:44:04.719
Stand.

1:44:08.426 --> 1:44:09.484
Stand!

1:44:11.796 --> 1:44:12.888
Stand...

1:44:13.164 --> 1:44:15.894
...all you who defiled
your sacred marriage beds...

1:44:16.167 --> 1:44:18.567
...and declare your sin.
Stand up...

1:44:18.770 --> 1:44:19.862
...with me...

1:44:20.138 --> 1:44:22.971
...as we stood against
our enemies at sea!

1:44:33.684 --> 1:44:34.708
There.

1:44:35.920 --> 1:44:37.478
You see, Your Grace...

1:44:38.489 --> 1:44:40.787
...there are no accomplices.

1:44:40.992 --> 1:44:43.654
He does this to rescue her
from your justice.

1:44:43.861 --> 1:44:48.594
Then I stand alone for Venice
and for this woman.

1:44:53.004 --> 1:44:55.097
His trial will commence tomorrow.

1:45:03.548 --> 1:45:04.674
Minister.

1:45:05.550 --> 1:45:06.710
Do you wish to speak?

1:45:09.487 --> 1:45:12.217
I repeat, do you have something
to say to this court?

1:45:14.225 --> 1:45:15.692
I am standing.

1:45:50.127 --> 1:45:51.151
Your Grace.

1:45:57.068 --> 1:45:59.195
Perhaps there's another
who'd like to stand?

1:46:13.217 --> 1:46:16.380
Perhaps we've been hasty, Your Grace.

1:46:16.921 --> 1:46:17.979
What are you doing?

1:46:18.556 --> 1:46:21.150
Witchcraft may be too harsh a charge.

1:46:28.566 --> 1:46:30.033
Is everything...

1:46:30.301 --> 1:46:31.928
...I heard about this city true?

1:46:32.770 --> 1:46:37.298
Surely the Holy Inquisition need not
sully its hands with a common whore.

1:46:38.910 --> 1:46:42.175
This is a matter for the state,
don't you think?

1:46:57.261 --> 1:46:58.728
I leave this woman to Venice...

1:47:01.265 --> 1:47:03.062
...which richly deserves her.
